						<summary>

						

						<p>On a slab near the platform of the flag-staff in front of the Chennarāyasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1530, Plavaṅga, Āshāḍha śu. 11 = 1607 A.D., June 25.</hi> The month was Adhika Āshāḍha and the Śaka year was current.</p>						

						<p>It states that while Pōtinēṁḍu, grandson of Pōtinēṁni, was ruling from Miriyāla, built a central shrine (?) for god Chaṁnnakēśavarāya and set up a lamp-pillar <hi rend="italic">(tiruvaḷike-kaṁbha)</hi> for the merit of his father Māṁchinēṁni and mother Māṁdama. Also records a grove raised by him.</p>						

						</summary>
